verbose_text: In this study, we showed that (i) AMH decreased similarly in both treatment groups, although Lz induced gonadotrophin secretion while low-dose T suppressed it; (ii) treatment induced changes in circulating gonadotrophin levels were not associated with the changes in serum AMH, while they correlated with changes in iB; and that (iii) varying Lz-levels, largely explained by Lz dose per weight (mg/kg), were not associated to HPG-axis activity or patient reported side effects.
